Zumpt suggests that, even if it existed, he may not have had occasion to visit it, as Albinus opened the hospitality of his villa to him. Such importance as the place possessed passed to Rosignano, about four miles distant, a village first mentioned in the second half of the eighth century. Rutilius describes the sandbanks that make the place difficult of access, yet afford shelter from rough weather for such vessels as are small enough to enter within them.
